<H2>Vitae</H2>
After earning a Masters degree of Computer Engineering from 
<!WA2><A HREF="http://www.lth.se/">Lund Institute of Technology</A>, 
<!WA3><A HREF="http://www-cse.ucsd.edu/users/markus/sverige.jpg">Sweden</A>,
I entered the 
<!WA4><A HREF="http://www-cse.ucsd.edu/cse/Graduate_Program.html">
PhD program in Computer Science</A> 
at 
<!WA5><A HREF="http://www-cse.ucsd.edu/cse/Around_Campus.html">University of California, San Diego</A>.
My research interest is cryptography; more specifically, 
digital cash and related issues like identification, signatures, 
distributed systems, zero-knowledge protocols and efficient protocols.
Click <!WA6><A HREF="http://www-cse.ucsd.edu/users/markus/cv.ps">here</A>
for a more detailed vitae.

